                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3k64bd2b/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>numerous resolutions adopted by various bodies<lb/> at the\n                    <placeName>North</placeName> shall be carried into effect. There<lb/> can be no\n                separate action allowed, and the prob-<lb/>ability is that, in endeavouring to give\n                satisfaction<lb/> to all, <sic>offence</sic> may be taken in some quarter. I<lb/>\n                shall be satisfied with whatever arrangements<lb/> will be made; tho' as yet I do\n                not even know,<lb/> whether I shall be permitted to be present.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I am really sorry to hear you speak in<lb/> so despondent a strain.\n                Is there nothing in your<lb/> present independent position to counterbalance\n                the<lb/> unjust treatment you have experienced? Think<lb/> for a moment, you were to\n                deliver a sermon “On<lb/> the disappointments incident to human life.”<lb/> Would it\n                not be a principal point, to exhort your<lb/> hearers to courage and perseverance\n                and to warn<lb/> them against despondency? You would probably say,<lb/> “As long as\n                your heart is good and your intentions<lb/> are pure, you need not complain, nor\n                fear.<lb/> The approbation of your conscience, and the coun-<lb/>tenance of the\n                almighty, will preserve your in-<lb/>ward peace amidst the most\n                    <sic>harrassing</sic> occur-<lb/>rences. Vain, hollow and thanging<add>?</add>\n                is the applause<lb/> of man. Take it for what it is worth, fret not<lb/> when it is\n                withheld, or bestowed on unworthy ob-<lb/>jects.” I am sure, you would present the\n                subject</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3k64bd2b/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
